---
title: Peach and Tomato Tartines with Ricotta, Mint, and Almonds
description: Kiss ordinary toast goodbye and say HELLO to tartines, or French open-faced sandwiches. This one’s topped with creamy ricotta, caramelized fruits, and summery greens. It’s practically a no-cook meal, which means you’ll be “toasting” to dinnertime in under 30 minutes.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/peach-and-tomato-tartines-b05ffd25.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/peach-and-tomato-tartines-e70ac8e8.pdf
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 493 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 56 g
  sugar: 27 g
  protein: 16 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 288 mg
servings: 2
time required: 25 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/peach-and-tomato-tartines-575eb9464dab714b528b4567
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees. Halve, pit, and slice the @peach{1}(halved, pitted, sliced into wedges) into wedges. Core and slice the @tomato{1}(cored and sliced into thin wedges) into thin wedges. Thinly slice the @mint{1/4%ounce}(thinly sliced).

Place the peach and tomato wedges on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in the oven for ~{4-6%minutes}, until the peaches and tomatoes are softened and slightly charred.

Toast the bread: Thinly slice the @wheat demi-baguette{1}(thinly sliced on a diagonal). Place the slices onto a baking sheet and drizzle with @olive oil{}. Place in the oven for ~{2-3%minutes}, flipping halfway, until lightly golden brown.

Heat a #small pan{} over medium heat. Add the @almonds{1%ounce} to the pan and cook, tossing, for ~{2-3%minutes}, until lightly golden brown and fragrant. Set aside.

Spread each toast with @ricotta cheese{5%ounce}, then top with a slice of peach and tomato. Finish each toast with mint and a drizzle of @honey{1%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Make the salad and serve: In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @balsamic vinegar{1%tablespoon}, @honey{1%tsp}, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{} (to taste). Season with salt and pepper. Toss the @arugula{4%ounce} and almonds into the dressing and serve alongside the peach and tomato tartines. Enjoy!